The paper proposes a method for learning policies from few demonstrations using a probabilistic grammar and logical program policies. This involves both machine learning and natural language processing techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, and cs.PL. Additionally, the experiments involve strategy games played on a 2D grid, which suggests a possible association with the sub-category of cs.CV (computer vision). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.PL, in that order.
